# Copy to `.env` and adjust. Changes require Metro restart (`npx expo start -c`).
#
# On a physical device, `localhost` / `127.0.0.1` refer to the phone — not your Mac.
# Options:
# (1) USB: `adb reverse tcp:3000 tcp:3000` then use https://127.0.0.1:3000 (mkcert must trust; install CA on device per CLAUDE.md).
# (2) Same WiFi: set your computer LAN IP, e.g. https://192.168.0.10:3000 — regenerate passkeys-server/certs
#     with: mkcert localhost 127.0.0.1 ::1 YOUR_LAN_IP
#     and point the server to the new .pem / update symlinks; server already listens on 0.0.0.0.
# Android emulator: often https://10.0.2.2:3000 — that hostname must be in the TLS cert or TLS will fail.
#
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://192.168.0.10:3000
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://localhost:3000
